Algorithm 1 Group Optimization for Multi-Task Alignment (GO4Align)   
1: Input: Maximum iteration number $T$ ; Batch size $N_{\mathrm{bz}}$ ; Learning rate $\alpha$ ; Temperature hyperparameter $\beta$ ; Task number $M$ ; Group number $(1<K\leq M)$ ;   
2: Initialize model parameters $\pmb{\theta}_{0}=\{\pmb{\theta}_{0}^{s},\pmb{\theta}_{0}^{1},\pmb{\theta}_{0}^{2},\cdots,\pmb{\theta}_{0}^{M}\}$ ;   
3: for $t=0:T$ do   
4: Randomly sample a batch of training samples: $\{(\mathbf{x}_{n},y_{n}^{1},...,y_{n}^{M})\}_{n=1}^{N_{\mathrm{bz}}}$ ,where $\pmb{x}_{n}\in\mathcal{X},y_{n}^{m}\in\mathcal{Y}^{m}$ ;   
5: Compute the empiric=al risk for each task at the $t$ -th iteration: $\begin{array}{r}{\hat{\mathcal{L}}^{m}(\bar{\pmb{\theta}}_{t}^{s},\pmb{\theta}_{t}^{m})=\frac{\bar{\bf\Phi}_{1}}{N_{\mathrm{bz}}}\sum_{n=1}^{N_{\mathrm{bz}}}\ell^{m}\big(f(\pmb{x}_{n};\pmb{\theta}_{t}^{s},\pmb{\theta}_{t}^{m}),y_{n}^{m}\big);}\end{array}$ ; // Lower-level optimization for grouping-based task interactions.   
6: Compute the scale vector $\mathcal{P}_{t}(\pmb{\theta}_{t})$ in Eq. (5);   
7: Compute the smoothness vector $\mathcal{Q}_{t}(\pmb{\theta}_{1:t})$ in Eq. (6);   
8: Obtain the group indicators $\gamma_{t}(\pmb\theta_{1:t})$ wi∶th Eq.(7);   
9: Update the group information $\omega_{t}$ ∶and $\textstyle\mathcal{G}_{t}$ with Eq. (3) and the obtained $\gamma_{t}(\pmb\theta_{1:t})$ . // Upper-level optimization for model parameters.   
10: Update the model parameters $\pmb{\theta}$ with Eq. (4): $\pmb{\theta}_{t+1}\leftarrow\operatorname{argmin}_{\pmb{\theta}}\omega_{t}\top\pmb{\mathcal{G}}_{t}\hat{L}(\pmb{\theta}).$   
11: end for
